parameters: \n< Shopkeeper >Welcome...

\n< Shopkeeper >What, are you a child? If you want to play, do it
outside.

\n< Serena >I'm not a child. I'm a customer. I also have an
adventurer's license.

\n< Serena >I want to purchase equipment. Can you show me your
selection?
\n< Shopkeeper >...You have money, right?

\n< Serena >Hmm... these items are quite unreliable, but I
guess I have no choice but to make do with them
for now.

\n< Shopkeeper >Oh, so you're saying my products are unreliable,
huh? Do you have any complaints about my
merchandise?

\n< Serena >Ah, I-I'm sorry. I blurted out something rude. It
just...

\n< Shopkeeper >Did you just say, 'I accidentally spoke the
truth'?

\n< Serena >Ugh... Mm, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to speak ill
of you, Shopkeeper-sama.

\n< Serena >However, this ring is insufficient to be used as
my weapon.
\n< Shopkeeper >Huh... A weapon? You're talking about a weapon.

\n< Shopkeeper >When you say weapon, it refers to things like
swords, axes, and these iron lumps.

\n< Shopkeeper >It's troublesome, isn't it? Mixing fairy tales and
reality, and complaining about my products.

\n< Serena >...The truth is the truth. I will use this ring as
my weapon. Your swords and axes cannot withstand
my magical power.

\n< Shopkeeper >You still want to say more! If you're going to say
that much, then here, take it and try holding it.

\n< Shopkeeper >How about comparing this iron lump that you're
making fun of, which is heavy, sturdy, and a
dangerous weapon, with that ring?

\n< Serena >If I can prove that this sword is useless, will
you believe what I say?

\n< Shopkeeper >Hahaha... Well, if you can prove that, then I'll
eat anything, even porridge made from cock.
\n< Shopkeeper >Huh...?
\n< Serena >Cough... It was more fragile than I thought...

\n< Serena >I apologize, Shopkeeper-sama. I scattered the
fragments. Are you injured?

\n< Shopkeeper >A... Oh, ah... Y-you, what the hell... Could it
be, a witch...?!

\n< Shopkeeper >What do you think you're doing coming to my shop?!
And on top of that, you went and broke an
important product... You better compensate for it!

\n< Shopkeeper >...No, no, that's not it.... I see, it's
interference?! It must be that bastard Henry's
doing...!

\n< Serena >No, no. Ah, why did it turn out like this? I just
wanted to go shopping...

\n< Serena >I'm sorry. I didn't mean to surprise you. Really.
I will compensate for the weapon as well.
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},"Paid 100G.",null)
\n< Shopkeeper >Huh...!? A, a bag of gold coins...?
\n< Serena >I-I'm sorry, excuse me...
\n< Shopkeeper >Hey, wait...! This much money--.

\n< Serena >*Sigh*... I was surprised... I wonder if
conversations can be this difficult.

\n< Serena >No, now that I think about it, it was my first
time having a conversation on equal terms with a
merchant.

\n< Serena >It feels completely different talking through a
servant... Maybe that's why I ended up angering
him.

\n< Serena >Anyway, I was able to obtain the ring. With this,
I can complete the quest.
\n< Serena >Let's go to the guild.
\n< Serena >.......

parameters:
\n< Shopkeeper >Welcome... What can I do for you, miss? We don't
have any rings beyond that.

\n< Serena >I apologize, but now is not the time for that.
Excuse me.

\n< Serena >This time it's for a different purpose. Actually,
I want to have a breastplate made...

\n< Shopkeeper >A breastplate? Well, of course we have some, but
when it comes to finding one that matches your
size, miss...

\n< Serena >No, when I say breastplate, I don't mean armor...
It's just that...

\n< Serena >To protect the delicate parts of my chest... with
a soft and gentle feeling...

\n< Shopkeeper >Ah, you mean a bra? If you want something like
that, go to the tool shop next door.

\n< Serena >...I went there, but there was nothing that suited
my skin.

\n< Serena >You are a weapons shop, aren't you? If you can
make weapons, can't you also make undergarments?

\n< Shopkeeper >...You're saying it lightly, but making something
like that... weapons and bras are quite different
genres.
\n< Shopkeeper >Well, I can do it.
\n< Serena >Oh!

\n< Shopkeeper >However, don't expect it to look good. It will
just be an extension of armor, after all.
\n< Serena >That's enough!
\n< Shopkeeper >Well, wait a moment.

\n< Shopkeeper >I happened to have a roll of silk left over. How
about this?

\n< Serena >Ah, ... I see. If it has this kind of texture, I
can tolerate it.

\n< Shopkeeper >With this, you can finally endure it. It's
supposed to be a top-notch product though...
\n< Shopkeeper >Well, fine. Then hold the other side.

\n< Shopkeeper >Sew the corners together, flip it inside out, and
pass it through.

\n< Shopkeeper >I threaded the string through, making small
stitches.
\n< Serena >Mmm... Oh, oh...?

\n< Shopkeeper >Alright, it's done. I think this size is just
right... What do you think?

\n< Serena >You have excellent skills... Perhaps you are more
suited to be a seamstress.

\n< Shopkeeper >You're still a talkative brat, huh... Any woman
around here could do this much.

\n< Shopkeeper >Well, fine. Why don't you try it on in that
fitting room over there?
\n< Serena >Mmm... Yes.

\n< Shopkeeper >Well, well, you cheeky little brat. Let me take a
look and see if you even have a body that needs a
bra.

\n< Shopkeeper >Hmhmhm, just as I thought, a delicate and
uninteresting body, huh?

\n< Shopkeeper >You're flaunting that flat chest of yours and
acting all grown-up, wanting a bra. You're ten
years too early for that.

\n< Shopkeeper >......H-hey...... Your... flat... chest... isn't
even worth peeking at....
\n< Shopkeeper >.........uhhh.

\n< Shopkeeper >...What whiteness. You're small, but there's flesh
on your ass too...
\n< Shopkeeper >Well...

\n< Serena >......Hmm. It's a bit rough and slightly big, but
if it's just this much, it's within an acceptable
range.

\n< Serena >Shopkeeper, it looks like this will be fine. I
appreciate you accommodating my request.
\n< Shopkeeper >.......
\n< Serena >Shopkeeper...?
\n< Shopkeeper >Huh? Ah...
\n< Serena >Um... So, I would like to pay the fee.
\n< Shopkeeper >M-Money?
\n< Shopkeeper >Ah, I see. Money, money.

\n< Shopkeeper >Well, you see. After all, we use the finest silk.
Well... I guess it would be around 100G.
\n< Serena >Understood. Let's pay.
\n< Shopkeeper >H-Huh...?
\n< Serena >What is it?

\n< Shopkeeper >It's 100G, you know? A hundred gold coins. It's
the kind of money that can build a house. If it's
small, you could even buy a ship.

\n< Shopkeeper >You... Yes, that's right. The money bag from the
other day. It also had 100G inside.

\n< Shopkeeper >In other words, it's a total of 200G. That's
enough to buy two houses or two ships. It's an
incredible amount of money. To just casually throw
around that kind of thing...
\n< Serena >B-But... Didn't you just say it was 100G?
\n< Shopkeeper >....
\n< Shopkeeper >...sigh...
\n< Shopkeeper >Ah, I see. 100G. I'll sell that bra for 100G.
\n< Serena >Understood. Let's pay.
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},"Paid 100G.",null)
\n< Shopkeeper >H-Huh...?

\n< Serena >What's wrong with you? You've been acting strange
since earlier...?
\n< Shopkeeper >Idiot... I've had enough of this stupidity...

\n< Shopkeeper >Even earning a single gold coin, we've been
sweating and working since morning... working,
working...

\n< Shopkeeper >If I could earn one gold coin in a day, it would
be a huge profit. But most of it ends up being
spent on living expenses, and I don't have
anything left in my hands.

\n< Shopkeeper >Treating this gold coin like some kind of toy...
as if it's just pocket change...
\n< Serena >Hm, huh...?

\n< Serena >I apologize, have I done something to upset you
again, Shopkeeper-sama?
\n< Shopkeeper >....
\n< Shopkeeper >No, no. It was quite a substantial transaction.

\n< Shopkeeper >There shouldn't be any complaints. Please, feel
free to come again anytime.

\n< Shopkeeper >Whether it's bras, panties, or pacifiers, I'll do
my best to have everything ready for you.

\n< Serena >Ugh... I can't help but feel like there's some
hidden meaning behind your attitude...

\n< Serena >Well, it's fine. Shopkeeper-sama... um, may I ask
for your name soon?
\n< Gordon >I'm Gordon.
\n< Serena >So you're Gordon-sama. I'm Serena.

\n< Serena >If anything happens again, please take care of me,
Lord Gordon.

\n< Gordon >Ah, please favor me. You have a nice ass, Serena-
sama.
"  The problem was solved for just 100G.\n  I can now resume my work. Let's go to the guild."
